The paper deals with learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). It also involves optimization and machine learning (cs.LG), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper's focus on optimizing diverse rankings suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and its consideration of document similarity and ranking context suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL).
